

The Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) provides advice about risks of travel to help British nationals make informed decisions. Find out more about FCDO travel advice. 
Earthquakes and tsunami at the Noto Peninsula
A series of earthquakes hit the Noto Peninsula on 1 January 2024, causing minor tsunami, several fires and major infrastructure damage in various parts of Ishikawa Prefecture. Further aftershocks remain a possibility and transport links are disrupted. If you are in the affected areas of the Noto Peninsula, follow the instructions from the local authorities and monitor the media for updates. You can also check for information on the Ishikawa Prefectural Government website. 
Further information on earthquakes and tsunamis can be found on the Japan Meteorological Agency website and the Japan National Tourism Agency website.
Before you travel
No travel can be guaranteed safe. Read all the advice in this guide and any specific travel advice that applies to you:
women travellers
disabled travellers
LGBT+ travellers
Follow and contact FCDO travel on Twitter, Facebook and Instagram. You can also sign up to get email notifications when this advice is updated. 
Travel insurance
If you choose to travel, research your destinations and get appropriate travel insurance. Insurance should cover your itinerary, planned activities and expenses in an emergency.
